: a Dormouse was sitting
  between them, fast asleep, and the other two were
  using it as a cushion, resting their elbows on it,
  and talking over its head. 'Very uncomfortable for
  the Dormouse,' thought Alice; 'only, as it's asleep, I
  suppose it doesn't mind.'

  The table was a large one, but the three were all
  sitting on the edge of it, with their legs dangling
  down into space. 'I wish they'd get tea ready,'
  thought Alice, 'and hand round the
  refreshments!'

  She waited for some time without hearing anything
  but a hoarse murmur from the Dormouse, who seemed to be
  snoring loud enough to fill the whole garden. At last
  she heard a sigh from the Hatter, and every one looked up
  at him. 'The time has come,'
